name: src/container.js
src/index.js

params.name: pattern
params.description: The pattern for the generated route.

params.name: action
params.description: The function the route performs if matched

name: action
description:
Calls the action that was passed from the constructor

************

name: match
description:
Checks if the url matches the route.
***

name: getRoute
description:
Generates the route that can be used to test if there is a match in a url;

******

name: getPattern
description:
Gets the pattern for the route. This will include all of the parents url as well.
****

name: Router
description: Gemerates a Router parent. This can be used to add more to the main router

return.description:
used to unregister an added route

***

name: PostRouteAction
description: Allows only post navigation. This class is used when app.post is used

name: GetRouterAction
description: Allows for Get Request navigation. used by app.get method

name: Application
description:
This is the main application route. It is also the route that everything will be linked to.
This is used to create the server

name: setInstance
description: Allows the developer to set a singleton. They can then retrieve this value with getItem method

params.name: name
params.description:
The name of the item stored in the Application container.

*****

name: listen
description: Boots the application on a certain port and allows for a callback once the application is running

params.name: port
params.description: The port number to start the server on

params.name: callback
params.description: The callback function to run onces the application has booted.
